00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:02.850
The answer is ICD and CPT.

00:00:04.610 --> 00:00:09.770
NDC, codes for medications, would
be found on a claim for payment for

00:00:09.770 --> 00:00:12.130
that medication, but ICD and

00:00:12.130 --> 00:00:18.180
CPT would be used to obtain payment for
physician offices.

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:21.320
The ICD states what problem was seen.

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:23.330
The CPT states what was done.

